@nft_insomnia024 And we will continue to do so

Until the WC is over and then we will go back to our sports that have more sensible rules

IMO the problem isn’t soccer the game it’s the format. World Cup appeals to Americans bc 1) easy to understand format 2) has all the star players competing in one place 3) the stakes are high. The NBA, NFL and MLB offer all these things too while league soccer seems splintered and confusing, not worth effort to follow. Fix/simplify the format and soccer will grow here. I’m gonna get blown up for this take but it’s my truth :)

@punk9059 Popular in America = more money

@DamirWallener Agree.. reg season is like a super expanded Group Stage. But we know you need to win some to make it to playoffs. So it's very similar to WC in a way

Me when someone tries to explain that Champions League is the answer but that league isnt their main league which it overlaps with and why come Messi isn't playing against Ronaldo or Neymar against Mbappe or anyone else I heard of https://t.co/2TIOTubwjA

@mitchelltweets2 Fair.  I’m just replying to the guy who was like baffled as to how soccer not bigger deal in America ex World Cup

@cullenroche That's also annoying. I was wartching the other day and I can't tell what is real and what is acting. I think 80% is acting and some of them are like Daniel Day Lewis in their commitment to the role. Tbf NBA is bad in this dept too but soccer is on another level

To everyone saying reg season NBA or MLB are not high stakes, you have a point. However, they are an appetizer (akin to Group Stage) bf main course (playoffs) but at least it is ONE league and ONE season and ONE place w best players in world. But yeah, tbf, reg season NBA and MLB suck, NFL better bc less games tho.

